57// Whether we are loading a property or storing to a property.
58// For a store during literal creation, do not walk up the prototype chain.
59// For a define operation, we behave similarly to kStoreInLiteral, but with
60// distinct semantics for private class fields (in which private field
61// accesses must throw when storing a field which does not exist, or
62// adding/defining a field which already exists).
63enum class AccessMode { kLoad, kStore, kStoreInLiteral, kHas, kDefine };
64
65inline bool IsAnyStore(AccessMode mode) {
66 return mode == AccessMode::kStore || mode == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral ||
67 mode == AccessMode::kDefine;
68}
69
70inline bool IsDefiningStore(AccessMode mode) {
71 return mode == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral || mode == AccessMode::kDefine;
72}

86#undef FOR_HOLE
87
88 kGeneric = kTheHole,
89};

91enum class RefSerializationKind {
92 // Skips serialization.
93 kNeverSerialized,
94 // Can be serialized on demand from the background thread.
95 kBackgroundSerialized,

267// Wrapper around heap refs which works roughly like a base::Optional, but
268// doesn't use extra storage for a boolean, but instead uses a null data pointer
269// as a sentinel no value.
270template <typename TRef>
271class OptionalRef {
272 public:
273 // {ArrowOperatorHelper} is returned by {OptionalRef::operator->}. It should
274 // never be stored anywhere or used in any other code; no one should ever have
275 // to spell out {ArrowOperatorHelper} in code. Its only purpose is to be
276 // dereferenced immediately by "operator-> chaining". Returning the address of
277 // the field is valid because this objects lifetime only ends at the end of
278 // the full statement.
279 class ArrowOperatorHelper {
280 public:
281 TRef* operator->() { return &object_; }
282
283 private:
284 friend class OptionalRef<TRef>;
285 explicit ArrowOperatorHelper(TRef object) : object_(object) {}
286
287 TRef object_;
288 };
289
290 OptionalRef() = default;
291 // NOLINTNEXTLINE
292 OptionalRef(base::nullopt_t) : OptionalRef() {}
293
294 // Allow implicit upcasting from OptionalRefs with compatible refs.
295 template <typename SRef, typename = typename std::enable_if<
296 std::is_convertible<SRef*, TRef*>::value>::type>
297 // NOLINTNEXTLINE
298 V8_INLINE OptionalRef(OptionalRef<SRef> ref) : data_(ref.data_) {}
299
300 // Allow implicit upcasting from compatible refs.
301 template <typename SRef, typename = typename std::enable_if<
302 std::is_convertible<SRef*, TRef*>::value>::type>
303 // NOLINTNEXTLINE
304 V8_INLINE OptionalRef(SRef ref) : data_(ref.data_) {}
305
306 constexpr bool has_value() const { return data_ != nullptr; }
307 constexpr explicit operator bool() const { return has_value(); }
308
309 TRef value() const {
310 DCHECK(has_value());
311 return TRef(data_, false);
312 }
313 TRef operator*() const { return value(); }
314 ArrowOperatorHelper operator->() const {
315 return ArrowOperatorHelper(value());
316 }
317
318 bool equals(OptionalRef other) const { return data_ == other.data_; }
319
320 size_t hash_value() const {
321 return has_value() ? value().hash_value() : base::hash_value(0);
322 }
323
324 private:
325 explicit OptionalRef(ObjectData* data) : data_(data) {
326 CHECK_NOT_NULL(data_);
327 }
328 ObjectData* data_ = nullptr;
329
330 template <typename SRef>
331 friend class OptionalRef;
332};
333
334template <typename T>
335inline bool operator==(OptionalRef<T> lhs, OptionalRef<T> rhs) {
336 return lhs.equals(rhs);
337}
338
339template <typename T>
340inline size_t hash_value(OptionalRef<T> ref) {
341 return ref.hash_value();
342}

413};

433// Temporary class that carries information from a Map. We'd like to remove
434// this class and use MapRef instead, but we can't as long as we support the
435// kDisabled broker mode. That's because obtaining the MapRef via
436// HeapObjectRef::map() requires a HandleScope when the broker is disabled.
437// During OptimizeGraph we generally don't have a HandleScope, however. There
438// are two places where we therefore use GetHeapObjectType() instead. Both that
439// function and this class should eventually be removed.
440class HeapObjectType {
441 public:
442 enum Flag : uint8_t { kUndetectable = 1 << 0, kCallable = 1 << 1 };
443
444 using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>;
445
446 HeapObjectType(InstanceType instance_type, ElementsKind elements_kind,
447 Flags flags, OddballType oddball_type, HoleType hole_type)
448 : instance_type_(instance_type),
449 elements_kind_(elements_kind),
450 oddball_type_(oddball_type),
451 hole_type_(hole_type),
452 flags_(flags) {
453 DCHECK_EQ(instance_type == ODDBALL_TYPE,
454 oddball_type != OddballType::kNone);
455 }
456
457 OddballType oddball_type() const { return oddball_type_; }
458 HoleType hole_type() const { return hole_type_; }
459 // For compatibility with MapRef.
460 OddballType oddball_type(JSHeapBroker* broker) const { return oddball_type_; }
461 HoleType hole_type(JSHeapBroker* broker) const { return hole_type_; }
462 InstanceType instance_type() const { return instance_type_; }
463 Flags flags() const { return flags_; }
464 ElementsKind elements_kind() const { return elements_kind_; }
465
466 bool is_callable() const { return flags_ & kCallable; }
467 bool is_undetectable() const { return flags_ & kUndetectable; }
468
469 private:
470 InstanceType const instance_type_;
471 ElementsKind const elements_kind_;
472 OddballType const oddball_type_;
473 HoleType const hole_type_;
474 Flags const flags_;
475};

477// Constructors are carefully defined such that we do a type check on
478// the outermost Ref class in the inheritance chain only.
479#define DEFINE_REF_CONSTRUCTOR(Name, Base) \
480 explicit Name##Ref(ObjectData* data, bool check_type = true) \
481 : Base(data, false) { \
482 if (check_type) { \
483 CHECK(Is##Name()); \
484 } \
485 }

528class JSObjectRef : public JSReceiverRef {
529 public:
530 DEFINE_REF_CONSTRUCTOR(JSObject, JSReceiverRef)
531
532 Handle<JSObject> object() const;
533
534 OptionalObjectRef raw_properties_or_hash(JSHeapBroker* broker) const;
535
536 // Usable only for in-object properties. Only use this if the underlying
537 // value can be an uninitialized-sentinel. Otherwise, use the higher-level
538 // GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty/GetOwnFastConstantDoubleProperty.
539 OptionalObjectRef RawInobjectPropertyAt(JSHeapBroker* broker,
540 FieldIndex index) const;
541
542 // Return the element at key {index} if {index} is known to be an own data
543 // property of the object that is non-writable and non-configurable. If
544 // {dependencies} is non-null, a dependency will be taken to protect
545 // against inconsistency due to weak memory concurrency.
546 OptionalObjectRef GetOwnConstantElement(
547 JSHeapBroker* broker, FixedArrayBaseRef elements_ref, uint32_t index,
548 CompilationDependencies* dependencies) const;
549 // The direct-read implementation of the above, extracted into a helper since
550 // it's also called from compilation-dependency validation. This helper is
551 // guaranteed to not create new Ref instances.
552 base::Optional<Tagged<Object>> GetOwnConstantElementFromHeap(
553 JSHeapBroker* broker, Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements,
554 ElementsKind elements_kind, uint32_t index) const;
555
556 // Return the value of the property identified by the field {index}
557 // if {index} is known to be an own data property of the object and the field
558 // is constant.
559 // If a property was successfully read, then the function will take a
560 // dependency to check the value of the property at code finalization time.
561 //
562 // This is *not* allowed to be a double representation field. Those should use
563 // GetOwnFastDoubleProperty, to avoid unnecessary HeapNumber allocation.
564 OptionalObjectRef GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
565 JSHeapBroker* broker, Representation field_representation,
566 FieldIndex index, CompilationDependencies* dependencies) const;
567
568 // Return the value of the double property identified by the field {index}
569 // if {index} is known to be an own data property of the object and the field
570 // is constant.
571 // If a property was successfully read, then the function will take a
572 // dependency to check the value of the property at code finalization time.
573 base::Optional<Float64> GetOwnFastConstantDoubleProperty(
574 JSHeapBroker* broker, FieldIndex index,
575 CompilationDependencies* dependencies) const;
576
577 // Return the value of the dictionary property at {index} in the dictionary
578 // if {index} is known to be an own data property of the object.
579 OptionalObjectRef GetOwnDictionaryProperty(
580 JSHeapBroker* broker, InternalIndex index,
581 CompilationDependencies* dependencies) const;
582
583 // When concurrent inlining is enabled, reads the elements through a direct
584 // relaxed read. This is to ease the transition to unserialized (or
585 // background-serialized) elements.
586 OptionalFixedArrayBaseRef elements(JSHeapBroker* broker,
587 RelaxedLoadTag) const;
588 bool IsElementsTenured(FixedArrayBaseRef elements);
589
590 OptionalMapRef GetObjectCreateMap(JSHeapBroker* broker) const;
591};

1235template <typename T>
1236struct ZoneCompactSetTraits<T, std::enable_if_t<compiler::is_ref<T>::value>> {
1237 using handle_type = T;
1238 using data_type = compiler::ObjectData;
1239
1240 static data_type* HandleToPointer(handle_type handle) {
1241 return handle.data();
1242 }
1243 static handle_type PointerToHandle(data_type* ptr) {
1244 return handle_type(ptr);
1245 }
1246};

1251using ZoneRefSet = ZoneCompactSet<typename ref_traits<T>::ref_type>;
1252
1253inline bool AnyMapIsHeapNumber(const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps) {
1254 return std::any_of(maps.begin(), maps.end(),
1255 [](MapRef map) { return map.IsHeapNumberMap(); });
1256}
1257
1258inline bool AnyMapIsHeapNumber(const base::Vector<const MapRef>& maps) {
1259 return std::any_of(maps.begin(), maps.end(),
1260 [](MapRef map) { return map.IsHeapNumberMap(); });
1261}
